  "prompt": "What is the exact truth behind Nikola Tesla and Thomas Edison rivalry?",
  "response": "The rivalry between Nikola Tesla and Thomas Edison is a complex historical narrative often simplified in popular culture. Here are the key facts:\n\n1. Professional Differences:\n- Edison was a practical, business-oriented inventor\n- Tesla was a theoretical, visionary engineer\n- They had fundamentally different approaches to electrical engineering\n\n2. \"War of Currents\":\n- Edison promoted direct current (DC) electrical systems\n- Tesla developed alternating current (AC) electrical systems\n- Tesla's AC system proved more efficient for long-distance power transmission\n- Edison tried to discredit AC by highlighting its potential dangers\n\n3. Employment History:\n- Tesla initially worked for Edison in 1884\n- He was promised $50,000 for improving Edison's DC generators\n- Edison allegedly didn't pay the full amount, leading to Tesla's resignation\n- This created personal animosity between them\n\n4. Business Competition:\n- Tesla partnered with George Westinghouse\n- They successfully demonstrated AC's superiority at the 1893 Chicago World's Fair\n- Eventually, AC became the standard electrical transmission system\n\n5. Personal Dynamics:\n- Edison was more commercially successful\n- Tesla was a brilliant inventor but struggled financially\n- Their rivalry was more professional than personal\n\nThe narrative is nuanced, with both inventors contributing significantly to electrical engineering's development.",
